'''Abdullah bin Mohammed bin Ali bin Abdullah Al Thani'''  is a member of [[Al Thani]] royal family of Qatar, who lived in the [[UAE]] (the country of his mother). He is the chairman of [[Sharjah International Airport]], [[Sharjah Airport International Free Zone]] and department of Civil Aviation in Sharjah; he is also chairman of [[Air Arabia]], the president of the [[Al-Sharjah Sports Club]], and the president of [[Sharjah Golf and Shooting Club]].

Abdullah is credited with enhancing the aviation industry in Sharjah, and UAE. He is also known for his generous contributions to Sharjah Sports Club.{{Citation needed|date= February 2012}}

