'''Signal Alliance''' is an [[Information technology|IT]] and [[Application service provider|Application Service Provider]] company, based in [[Nigeria]], with offices in [[Lagos]] and [[Abuja]].
== History == The company was founded in 1996 and started its operations the same year.<ref>[http://www.signalalliance.com/who-we-are/our-company/ Corporate Website - Who we are]</ref> The company's main activity was the sales of [[network switches]] before expanding its operation into [[software application]] based services.
The company has a Technology Investment subsidiary called Sasware which invests in technology companies.
The company also publishes reports on IT related topics and has issued warnings on malware through the media.{{cite web|title=Microsoft Partner Issues Ransomware Advisory|url=https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/news/business/microsoft-partner-issues-ransomware-advisory/198021.html|website=Daily Trust|publisher=Zakkariya Adaramola}}</ref>
The company has partnered with Microsoft and is authorised to sell Microsoft products and provide technical support. The company has also partnered with Cisco.
