[[Image:William black.jpg|thumb|right|Rev William Black by [[William Valentine (painter)]]]] '''William Black''' (November 10, 1760 &ndash; September 8, 1834) was a [[Migration from Yorkshire to Nova Scotia|Yorkshireman]] and founder of the [[Methodist Church, Canada|Methodist congregation]] in colonial Nova Scotia. [[File:PointDeButeLychGate.jpg|thumb|left|Cemetery in [[Point de Bute, New Brunswick]], near where the first Methodist church stood and where Black would have preached.]] Black's daughter married the merchant and politician [[John Alexander Barry]], who was the son of [[Robert Barry (merchant)|Robert Barry]], a prominent businessman and Methodist. His son, [[Martin Gay Black]], became a prominent businessman and also furthered the Methodist cause in Nova Scotia.
